modules.description: Provides functions to create, access, and transform arrays where each element may be absent, using a specialized representation that avoids boxing overhead. Works with arrays of optional values, supporting operations like mapping, filtering, and checking for presence. Useful for efficiently handling sparse data or optional fields in performance-critical code.

Provides operations to create, access, and modify arrays where elements can be absent, using a compact representation. Works with arrays of values that may be None, supporting indexed access, modification, and iteration. Used for efficiently handling sparse data structures or optional fields in memory-constrained scenarios.
